{"title_page": "Mewkledreamy", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese anime series}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name      = Mewkledreamy\n| image     =\n| caption   = \n| ja_kanji  = \u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30af\u30eb\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30df\u30fc\n| ja_romaji = My\u016bkurudor\u012bm\u012b\n| genre     = [[Fantasy]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = [[Hiroaki Sakurai]]\n| producer        = Yuuji Matsukura\n| writer          = Hiroko Kanasugi\n| music           = Ruka Kawada\n| studio          = [[J.C.Staff]]\n| licensee        = \n| network         = [[TX Network|TXN]] ([[TV Tokyo]], [[TV Osaka]]), [[AT-X (company)|AT-X]], [[Kids Station]]\n| network_en      = \n| first           = April 5, 2020\n| last            = \n| episodes        = <!-- This parameter should only be incremented when new episodes air or when a [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources|reliable source]] can confirm a specific number of episodes. -->\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = \n| publisher       = [[Kodansha]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Kodomo manga|Kodomo]]''\n| imprint         =\n| magazine        = Otomodachi, Tanoshii Y\u014dchien\n| first           = April 2020\n| last            = \n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{nihongo|'''''Mewkledreamy'''''|\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30af\u30eb\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30df\u30fc|My\u016bkurudor\u012bm\u012b|lead=yes}} is a character [[Media franchise|franchise]] created by [[Sanrio]], illustrated by character designer Mayumi Yanagita. The franchise was officially launched in 2017.\n\nAn [[Anime|anime]] television series adaptation by [[J.C.Staff]] premiered on all [[TX Network|TXN]] stations in [[Japan]] on April 5, 2020.\n\n==Story==\n===Franchise===\nMew is a light violet stuffed kitten created in a world from the sky by doll-making fairies. One day, she fell from the sky and was picked up by a human girl. The girl hugged and spoke with Mew every day. Hoping to express her gratitude to the girl, Mew made a wish to the moon. After the moonlight made Mew's star pattern in her ear shine, she began to be able to speak. Since then, Mew and the girl chat every day. They can have the same dream when they sleep together, while playing and exchanging secrets in the dream.\n\n===Anime===\nYume is a cheerful first-year junior high school student who by chance picked up Mew, a speaking kitten plush who fell from the sky. By becoming Dream Partners, Mew possesses the power of \"Dream Synchro\" and is able to enter one's dream along with Yume. That night, the queen of Miracle Dreamy Kingdom appeared in Yume's dream, telling her that if she and Mew collect a lot of Dreamy Stones, she can grant her one wish. Since then, Yume starts to collect Dreamy Stones with Mew, while enjoying her school life.\n\n==Characters from anime==\n===Stuffed kittens===\n;{{nihongo|Mew|\u307f\u3085\u30fc|My\u016b}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Aki Toyosaki]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:The main kitten protagonist, a light violet stuffed kitten. She is sweet and kind, and is afraid of dogs. She ends her sentences with \"~mya\". She possesses the power of \"Dream Synchro\", an ability to enter one's dream. She fell down from the sky one day and was picked up by Yume, thus becomes her Dream Partner.\n;{{nihongo|Peko|\u307a\u3053|Peko}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Yurika Kubo]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A light yellow stuffed kitten. He loves eating and making others laugh. He is Maira's partner.\n;{{nihongo|Suu|\u3059\u3046|S\u016b}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Hisako Kanemoto]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A light blue stuffed kitten. She is clever and gentle. She is Kotoko's partner.\n;{{nihongo|Yuni|\u3086\u306b|Yuni}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Rie Kugimiya]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A black stuffed kitten. He likes mischief, but is also quite clumsy. He is rival of Mew and co.. He treasures Tsugi and Hagi a lot. He ends his sentences with \"~nyui\".\n;{{nihongo|Tsugi|\u3064\u304e|Tsugi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Misaki Kuno]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A stuffed kitten created by Yuni. She likes Yuni a lot.\n;{{nihongo|Hagi|\u306f\u304e|Hagi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Natsumi Fujiwara]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A stuffed kitten created by Yuni. He likes Yuni a lot.\n\n===Humans===\n====Major====\n;{{nihongo|Yume Hinata|\u65e5\u5411 \u3086\u3081|Hinata Yume}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Natsumi Murakami (voice actress)|Natsumi Murakami]]<ref name=\"md\">{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy TV Anime Reveals Cast, More Staff, April Premiere|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-31/sanrio-mewkledreamy-tv-anime-reveals-cast-more-staff-april-premiere/.155969|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref>}}\n:The main human protagonist, a cheerful first-year junior high school student who plans to enter the cheerleading club. She owns a dog named \"Q-chan\". She does not like tomatoes. She by chance picks up Mew, becomes her Dream Partner, and starts collecting Dreamy Stones with her.\n\n;{{nihongo|Maira Tsukishima|\u6708\u5cf6 \u307e\u3044\u3089|Tsukishima Maira}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayasa It\u014d]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's classmate and Peko's partner. She is a model of a popular fashion magazine. She knows a lot about fashion, but also loves comedy, hoping to become a comedian one day. She plans to establish a comedy studying club in school.\n\n;{{nihongo|Kotoko Imai|\u4eca\u4e95 \u3053\u3068\u3053|Imai Kotoko}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Eri Yukimura]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A third-year junior high school student who is Yume's senior and Suu's partner. Her grade is the top of the third-years, and she is the president of the computer club. She is good at taking care of others.\n\n;{{nihongo|Asahi Minamikawa|\u5357\u5ddd \u671d\u967d|Minamikawa Asahi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u016bsuke Kobayashi (voice actor)|Y\u016bsuke Kobayashi]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's classmate and neighbour, as well as childhood friend. He is good at sports, and plans to enter the tennis club.\n\n;{{nihongo|Haruhito Sugiyama|\u6749\u5c71 \u907c\u4ec1|Sugiyama Haruhito}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Yuuki Ogoe]]<ref name=\"md2\">{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy TV Anime Reveals More Cast, Theme Song Artists, April 5 Premiere|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-26/sanrio-mewkledreamy-tv-anime-reveals-more-cast-theme-song-artists-april-5-premiere/.156886|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>}}\n:A third-year junior high school student who is Yume's senior. He is the president of the boys' tennis club and the student council. He is popular in school, and Yume has a crush on him.\n\n====Ichigo Junior High School====\n;{{nihongo|Yuri Sawamura|\u6ca2\u6751 \u767e\u5408|Sawamura Yuri}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kana Ichinose]]<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A third-year junior high school student who is Haruhito's classmate and childhood friend. She is the president of the calligraphy club and the vice-president of the student council.\n;{{nihongo|Wakaba Midorino|\u7dd1\u91ce \u308f\u304b\u3070|Midorino Wakaba}}\n:{{voiced by|Y\u016bki Hirose<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. She plans to enter the cheerleading club with Yume.\n;{{nihongo|Kaede Akana|\u8d64\u540d \u304b\u3048\u3067|Akana Kaede}}\n:{{voiced by|Ayumi Mano<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. She is well-informed on and likes to talk about romance gossips. She plans to enter the tennis club.\n;{{nihongo|Hana Shiraishi|\u767d\u77f3 \u306f\u306a|Shiraishi Hana}}\n:{{voiced by|Yuka Nukui<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. She loves drawing, and plans to enter the art club.\n;{{nihongo|Teacher Aoi|\u9752\u4e95\u5148\u751f|Aoi-sensei}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kazuyuki Okitsu]]}}\n:Yume's class teacher.\n;{{nihongo|Shouhei Kitada|\u5317\u7530 \u7fd4\u5e73|Kitada Shouhei}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Makoto Furukawa]]}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. He is a good friend of Asahi.\n;{{nihongo|Momiji Akana|\u8d64\u540d \u3082\u307f\u3058|Akana Momiji}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u014d Taichi]]}}\n:Kaede's older sister. She is the president of the girls' tennis club.\n;{{nihongo|Misaki|\u7f8e\u54b2|Misaki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[M\u30fbA\u30fbO]]}}\n:She is the president of the cheerleading club.\n;{{nihongo|Yui|\u7d50\u8863|Yui}}\n:{{voiced by|Saya Tanaka}}\n:She is a member of the cheerleading club.\n;{{nihongo|Oshio|\u62bc\u5c3e|Oshio}}\n:{{voiced by|Mayu Mineda}}\n:She is the president of the Sugiyama fan club.\n;{{nihongo|Yoshio Maruyama|\u4e38\u5c71 \u30e8\u30b7\u30aa|Maruyama Yoshio}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Sh\u014dya Chiba]]}}\n:He is a member of the student council.\n;{{nihongo|Suzuko Kakumoto|\u89d2\u672c \u30b9\u30ba\u5b50|Kakumoto Suzuko}}\n:{{voiced by|Maria Sawada}}\n:She is a member of the student council.\n\n===Miracle Dreamy Kingdom===\n;{{nihongo|The Queen|\u5973\u738b\u3055\u307e}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kikuko Inoue]]<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:The queen of Miracle Dreamy Kingdom. She appeared in Yume's dream and told her if she can collect a lot of Dreamy Stones with Mew, she can grant her one wish.\n\n==Media==\n===Anime===\nAn [[Anime|anime]] television series based on the toy franchise was announced at the Sanrio Expo 2019 to be animated by [[J.C.Staff]]. [[Chiaki Kon]]<ref>https://www.animatetimes.com/news/details.php?id=1567156215</ref> (''[[Golden Time (novel series)|Golden Time]]'', ''[[Devils and Realist]]'') was to direct the series with [[Natsumi Murakami (voice actress)|Natsumi Murakami]] be the first cast member to be announced.<ref name=\"xp\">{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy Character Gets Spring TV Anime by J.C. Staff|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-08-30/sanrio-mewkledreamy-character-gets-spring-tv-anime-by-j.c-staff/.150547|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 30, 2019|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref> On September 10, 2019, a promotional video released by Sanrio's [[YouTube]] channel introduced additional characters in the anime.<ref>{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy TV Anime Unveils Promo Video, Visual|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-09-10/sanrio-mewkledreamy-tv-anime-unveils-promo-video-visual/.150936|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref> On January 31, 2020, the anime's website that the anime would premiere in April.<ref name=\"md\"/> The site also announced ten more cast members and three more staff members,<ref name=\"md\"/> including Hiroko Kanasugi (''[[PriPara]]'', ''[[RobiHachi]]'') as writer and Mai Furuki (''[[Planet With]]'') as character designer. However Kon stepped down as director due to unknown issues and will remain in the project as Project Consultant. The directorial role will be filled out by [[Hiroaki Sakurai]] (''[[Di Gi Charat]]'', ''[[UFO Baby]]'', ''[[The Disastrous Life of Saiki K.]]'') instead.<ref>https://natalie.mu/comic/news/365368</ref> On February 27, 2020, the anime was confirmed to be premiere on April 5, 2020, and more cast members and characters, as well as the theme songs were announced.<ref name=\"md2\"/>\n\n==== Episode List ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF\"\n! style=\"width:3em;\" | No.\n! Title\n! style=\"width:125px;\"| Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 01\n| Title           = The Story of the Beginning\n| AltTitle        = Hajimari no sut\u014dr\u012b\n| RAltTitle       = &nbsp;({{Nihongo2|\u306f\u3058\u307e\u308a\u306e\u30b9\u30c8\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc}})\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|5}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 02\n| Title           = Trial Club Joining with Dream Synchro\n| AltTitle        = Yumeshinkuro de kari ny\u016bbu\n| RAltTitle       = &nbsp;({{Nihongo2|\u30e6\u30e1\u30b7\u30f3\u30af\u30ed\u3067\u4eee\u5165\u90e8}})\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|12}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 03\n| Title           = Let's Enter Senpai's Dream\n| AltTitle        = Senpai no yume ni haitchao\n| RAltTitle       = &nbsp;({{Nihongo2|\u5148\u8f29\u306e\u5922\u306b\u5165\u3063\u3061\u3083\u304a}})\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 04\n| Title           = Another Dreamy Mate?\n| AltTitle        = M\u014dhitori no dor\u012bm\u012b meito?\n| RAltTitle       = &nbsp;({{Nihongo2|\u3082\u3046\u4e00\u4eba\u306e\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30df\u30fc\u30e1\u30a4\u30c8\uff1f}})\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|26}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n|}\n\n===Music===\nMaria Sawada will perform both the series' opening theme {{Nihongo|\"Mirai Kuru Kuru Yume Kururu!\"|\u30df\u30e9\u30a4\u304f\u308b\u304f\u308b\u30e6\u30e1\u304f\u308b\u308b\uff01||\"Future's Coming,  Dream's Coming!\"|lead=yes}} and the ending theme {{Nihongo|\"Tokimeki Collector\"|\u30c8\u30ad\u30e1\u30ad\u30b3\u30ec\u30af\u30bf\u30fc|Tokimeki Korekut\u0101|\"Heartbeat Collector\"|lead=yes}}. The series's music is composed by Ruka Kawada (''[[The Idolmaster]]'' franchise).\n\n===Manga===\nA tie-in manga adaptation is being serialized in two of [[Kodansha]]'s magazines, ''Otomodachi'' and ''Tanoshii Y\u014dchien'', since April 2020 issue.<ref name=\"xp\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.sanrio.co.jp/character/mewkledreamy/ Sanrio's official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://mewkledreamy.com/ Official anime website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/mewkledreamy/ TV Tokyo anime website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|anime|22485}}\n\n{{Sanrio}}\n{{J.C.Staff}}\n\n[[Category:2020 manga]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about cats]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Fictional cats]]\n[[Category:J.C.Staff]]\n[[Category:Media franchises introduced in 2017]]\n[[Category:Sanrio characters]]\n[[Category:Sanrio]]\n[[Category:TV Tokyo shows]]\n\n{{Anime-tv-series-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese anime series}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name      = Mewkledreamy\n| image     =\n| caption   = \n| ja_kanji  = \u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30af\u30eb\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30df\u30fc\n| ja_romaji = My\u016bkurudor\u012bm\u012b\n| genre     = [[Fantasy]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = [[Hiroaki Sakurai]]\n| producer        = Yuuji Matsukura\n| writer          = Hiroko Kanasugi\n| music           = Ruka Kawada\n| studio          = [[J.C.Staff]]\n| licensee        = \n| network         = [[TX Network|TXN]] ([[TV Tokyo]], [[TV Osaka]]), [[AT-X]], [[Kids Station]]\n| network_en      = \n| first           = April 5, 2020\n| last            = \n| episodes        = <!-- This parameter should only be incremented when new episodes air or when a [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources|reliable source]] can confirm a specific number of episodes. -->\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = \n| publisher       = [[Kodansha]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Kodomo manga|Kodomo]]''\n| imprint         =\n| magazine        = Otomodachi, Tanoshii Y\u014dchien\n| first           = April 2020\n| last            = \n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{nihongo|'''''Mewkledreamy'''''|\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30af\u30eb\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30df\u30fc|My\u016bkurudor\u012bm\u012b|lead=yes}} is a character [[Media franchise|franchise]] created by [[Sanrio]], illustrated by character designer Mayumi Yanagita. The franchise was officially launched in 2017.\n\nAn [[Anime|anime]] television series adaptation by [[J.C.Staff]] premiered on all [[TX Network|TXN]] stations in [[Japan]] on April 5, 2020.\n\n==Story==\n===Franchise===\nMew is a light violet stuffed kitten created in a world from the sky by doll-making fairies. One day, she fell from the sky and was picked up by a human girl. The girl hugged and spoke with Mew every day. Hoping to express her gratitude to the girl, Mew made a wish to the moon. After the moonlight made Mew's star pattern in her ear shine, she began to be able to speak. Since then, Mew and the girl chat every day. They can have the same dream when they sleep together, while playing and exchanging secrets in the dream.\n\n===Anime===\nYume is a cheerful first-year junior high school student who by chance picked up Mew, a speaking kitten plush who fell from the sky. By becoming Dream Partners, Mew possesses the power of \"Dream Synchro\" and is able to enter one's dream along with Yume. That night, the queen of Miracle Dreamy Kingdom appeared in Yume's dream, telling her that if she and Mew collect a lot of Dreamy Stones, she can grant her one wish. Since then, Yume starts to collect Dreamy Stones with Mew, while enjoying her school life.\n\n==Characters from anime==\n===Stuffed kittens===\n;{{nihongo|Mew|\u307f\u3085\u30fc|My\u016b}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Aki Toyosaki]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:The main kitten protagonist, a light violet stuffed kitten. She is sweet and kind, and is afraid of dogs. She ends her sentences with \"~mya\". She possesses the power of \"Dream Synchro\", an ability to enter one's dream. She fell down from the sky one day and was picked up by Yume, thus becomes her Dream Partner.\n;{{nihongo|Peko|\u307a\u3053|Peko}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Yurika Kubo]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A light yellow stuffed kitten. He loves eating and making others laugh. He is Maira's partner.\n;{{nihongo|Suu|\u3059\u3046|S\u016b}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Hisako Kanemoto]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A light blue stuffed kitten. She is clever and gentle. She is Kotoko's partner.\n;{{nihongo|Yuni|\u3086\u306b|Yuni}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Rie Kugimiya]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A black stuffed kitten. He likes mischief, but is also quite clumsy. He is rival of Mew and co.. He treasures Tsugi and Hagi a lot. He ends his sentences with \"~nyui\".\n;{{nihongo|Tsugi|\u3064\u304e|Tsugi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Misaki Kuno]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A stuffed kitten created by Yuni. She likes Yuni a lot.\n;{{nihongo|Hagi|\u306f\u304e|Hagi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Natsumi Fujiwara]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A stuffed kitten created by Yuni. He likes Yuni a lot.\n\n===Humans===\n====Major====\n;{{nihongo|Yume Hinata|\u65e5\u5411 \u3086\u3081|Hinata Yume}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Natsumi Murakami (voice actress)|Natsumi Murakami]]<ref name=\"md\">{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy TV Anime Reveals Cast, More Staff, April Premiere|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-31/sanrio-mewkledreamy-tv-anime-reveals-cast-more-staff-april-premiere/.155969|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref>}}\n:The main human protagonist, a cheerful first-year junior high school student who plans to enter the cheerleading club. She owns a dog named \"Q-chan\". She does not like tomatoes. She by chance picks up Mew, becomes her Dream Partner, and starts collecting Dreamy Stones with her.\n\n;{{nihongo|Maira Tsukishima|\u6708\u5cf6 \u307e\u3044\u3089|Tsukishima Maira}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayasa It\u014d]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's classmate and Peko's partner. She is a model of a popular fashion magazine. She knows a lot about fashion, but also loves comedy, hoping to become a comedian one day. She plans to establish a comedy studying club in school.\n\n;{{nihongo|Kotoko Imai|\u4eca\u4e95 \u3053\u3068\u3053|Imai Kotoko}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Eri Yukimura]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A third-year junior high school student who is Yume's senior and Suu's partner. Her grade is the top of the third-years, and she is the president of the computer club. She is good at taking care of others.\n\n;{{nihongo|Asahi Minamikawa|\u5357\u5ddd \u671d\u967d|Minamikawa Asahi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u016bsuke Kobayashi (voice actor)|Y\u016bsuke Kobayashi]]<ref name=\"md\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's classmate and neighbour, as well as childhood friend. He is good at sports, and plans to enter the tennis club.\n\n;{{nihongo|Haruhito Sugiyama|\u6749\u5c71 \u907c\u4ec1|Sugiyama Haruhito}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Yuuki Ogoe]]<ref name=\"md2\">{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy TV Anime Reveals More Cast, Theme Song Artists, April 5 Premiere|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-26/sanrio-mewkledreamy-tv-anime-reveals-more-cast-theme-song-artists-april-5-premiere/.156886|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>}}\n:A third-year junior high school student who is Yume's senior. He is the president of the boys' tennis club and the student council. He is popular in school, and Yume has a crush on him.\n\n====Ichigo Junior High School====\n;{{nihongo|Yuri Sawamura|\u6ca2\u6751 \u767e\u5408|Sawamura Yuri}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kana Ichinose]]<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A third-year junior high school student who is Haruhito's classmate and childhood friend. She is the president of the calligraphy club and the vice-president of the student council.\n;{{nihongo|Wakaba Midorino|\u7dd1\u91ce \u308f\u304b\u3070|Midorino Wakaba}}\n:{{voiced by|Y\u016bki Hirose<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. She plans to enter the cheerleading club with Yume.\n;{{nihongo|Kaede Akana|\u8d64\u540d \u304b\u3048\u3067|Akana Kaede}}\n:{{voiced by|Ayumi Mano<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. She is well-informed on and likes to talk about romance gossips. She plans to enter the tennis club.\n;{{nihongo|Hana Shiraishi|\u767d\u77f3 \u306f\u306a|Shiraishi Hana}}\n:{{voiced by|Yuka Nukui<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. She loves drawing, and plans to enter the art club.\n;{{nihongo|Teacher Aoi|\u9752\u4e95\u5148\u751f|Aoi-sensei}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kazuyuki Okitsu]]}}\n:Yume's class teacher.\n;{{nihongo|Shouhei Kitada|\u5317\u7530 \u7fd4\u5e73|Kitada Shouhei}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Makoto Furukawa]]}}\n:A first-year junior high school student who is Yume's friend since grade school. He is a good friend of Asahi.\n;{{nihongo|Momiji Akana|\u8d64\u540d \u3082\u307f\u3058|Akana Momiji}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u014d Taichi]]}}\n:Kaede's older sister. She is the president of the girls' tennis club.\n;{{nihongo|Misaki|\u7f8e\u54b2|Misaki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[M\u30fbA\u30fbO]]}}\n:She is the president of the cheerleading club.\n;{{nihongo|Yui|\u7d50\u8863|Yui}}\n:{{voiced by|Saya Tanaka}}\n:She is a member of the cheerleading club.\n;{{nihongo|Oshio|\u62bc\u5c3e|Oshio}}\n:{{voiced by|Mayu Mineda}}\n:She is the president of the Sugiyama fan club.\n;{{nihongo|Yoshio Maruyama|\u4e38\u5c71 \u30e8\u30b7\u30aa|Maruyama Yoshio}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Sh\u014dya Chiba]]}}\n:He is a member of the student council.\n;{{nihongo|Suzuko Kakumoto|\u89d2\u672c \u30b9\u30ba\u5b50|Kakumoto Suzuko}}\n:{{voiced by|Maria Sawada}}\n:She is a member of the student council.\n\n===Miracle Dreamy Kingdom===\n;{{nihongo|The Queen|\u5973\u738b\u3055\u307e}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kikuko Inoue]]<ref name=\"md2\"/>}}\n:The queen of Miracle Dreamy Kingdom. She appeared in Yume's dream and told her if she can collect a lot of Dreamy Stones with Mew, she can grant her one wish.\n\n==Media==\n===Anime===\nAn [[Anime|anime]] television series based on the toy franchise was announced at the Sanrio Expo 2019 to be animated by [[J.C.Staff]]. [[Chiaki Kon]]<ref>https://www.animatetimes.com/news/details.php?id=1567156215</ref> (''[[Golden Time (novel series)|Golden Time]]'', ''[[Devils and Realist]]'') was to direct the series with [[Natsumi Murakami (voice actress)|Natsumi Murakami]] be the first cast member to be announced.<ref name=\"xp\">{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy Character Gets Spring TV Anime by J.C. Staff|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-08-30/sanrio-mewkledreamy-character-gets-spring-tv-anime-by-j.c-staff/.150547|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=August 30, 2019|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref> On September 10, 2019, a promotional video released by Sanrio's [[YouTube]] channel introduced additional characters in the anime.<ref>{{cite news|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|title=Sanrio's Mewkledreamy TV Anime Unveils Promo Video, Visual|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-09-10/sanrio-mewkledreamy-tv-anime-unveils-promo-video-visual/.150936|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref> On January 31, 2020, the anime's website that the anime would premiere in April.<ref name=\"md\"/> The site also announced ten more cast members and three more staff members,<ref name=\"md\"/> including Hiroko Kanasugi (''[[PriPara]]'', ''[[RobiHachi]]'') as writer and Mai Furuki (''[[Planet With]]'') as character designer. However Kon stepped down as director due to unknown issues and will remain in the project as Project Consultant. The directorial role will be filled out by [[Hiroaki Sakurai]] (''[[Di Gi Charat]]'', ''[[UFO Baby]]'', ''[[The Disastrous Life of Saiki K.]]'') instead.<ref>https://natalie.mu/comic/news/365368</ref> On February 27, 2020, the anime was confirmed to be premiere on April 5, 2020, and more cast members and characters, as well as the theme songs were announced.<ref name=\"md2\"/>\n\n==== Episode List ====\n{|class=\"wikitable