-in manga adaptation is being serialized in two of [[Kodansha]]'s magazines, ''Otomodachi'' and ''Tanoshii Y\u014dchien'', since April 2020 issue.<ref name=\"xp\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.sanrio.co.jp/character/mewkledreamy/ Sanrio's official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://mewkledreamy.com/ Official anime website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[https://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/mewkledreamy/ TV Tokyo anime website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|anime|22485}}\n\n{{Sanrio}}\n{{J.C.Staff}}\n\n[[Category:2020 manga]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about cats]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Fictional cats]]\n[[Category:J.C.Staff]]\n[[Category:Media franchises introduced in 2017]]\n[[Category:Sanrio characters]]\n[[Category:Sanrio]]\n[[Category:TV Tokyo shows]]\n\n{{Anime-tv-series-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Squids and Chips", "label": "safe", "comment": "DisambiguateAT-XtoAT-X (company)usingpopups", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mewkledreamy"}
{"title_page": "Addington Raceway", "text_new": "[[File:Addington Raceway, 2004.jpg|thumb|Addington Raceway in 2004]]\n'''Addington Raceway''' or '''The Met''' is the home of the Metropolitan Trotting Club in [[Addington, New Zealand|Addington]], [[Christchurch]] in New Zealand.  The venue consists of a trotting track, a greyhound track, conference centre and restaurants. It is also home to many feature harness races such as: The [[New Zealand Trotting Cup]] and the [[Dominion Handicap]].\n\nThe raceway forms part of a sporting complex that includes [[Rugby League Park]] and the [[CBS Canterbury Arena]].\n\n==History==\nThe NZ Metropolitan Trotting Club (NZMTC) was first based at [[Lancaster Park]] in [[Waltham, New Zealand|Waltham]].  [[Charles Louisson]], a steward of NZMTC and [[Mayor of Christchurch]] at the time,<ref name=\"NZETC\">{{cite book|title=The Cyclopedia of New Zealand (Canterbury Provincial District)|publisher=Cyclopedia Company Limited|location=Christchurch |year=1903|chapter=The Hon. Charles Louisson |url= http://www.nzetc.org/tm/scholarly/tei-Cyc03Cycl-t1-body1-d3-d9.html |accessdate=4 November 2011}}</ref> helped to secure land in [[Addington, New Zealand|Addington]] and in 1899, the club moved to the present site.  From 1906 until his death<ref>{{cite web|title=Presidents: NZMTC |url=http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=2&ID=20 |publisher=Addington Raceway |accessdate=4 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111225183058/http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=2&ID=20 |archivedate=25 December 2011 }}</ref> in 1924, he was the president of the NZMTC.  The grounds were enlarged during his presidency.<ref name=\"Louisson Handicap\">{{cite web|title=Mescellany |url=http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=6&ItemId=398&AlphaId=12&CategoryId=3 |publisher=Addington Raceway |accessdate=4 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130207074257/http://addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=6&ItemId=398&AlphaId=12&CategoryId=3 |archivedate=7 February 2013 }}</ref>  The Louisson Handicap was an annual race that was held for many years.  Between 1914 and 1923, Louisson annually donated the silver trophy for the New Zealand Trotting Cup, which he had manufactured in England.<ref>{{cite web|title=Racing History |url=http://www.addington.co.nz/timeline.asp?Case=1&ID=1921 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060929095613/http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=1&ID=1921 |url-status=dead |archive-date=29 September 2006 |publisher=Addington Raceway |accessdate=7 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Interdominions==\n\nAddington has hosted the Interdominions in 1938, 1951, 1961, 1971, 1979, 1987, 1995 and 2003. The 2011 series was planned to be at Addington but due to the 2011 Christchurch Earthquake was moved to Alexandra Park.\n\n==Motorcycling==\nAddington Raceway has also hosted the New Zealand Long Track Grand Prix for [[Motorcycle speedway]]. It first hosted the GP in 1991 and was won by Kiwi rider [[Mitch Shirra]]. It held the event again in 1992 when it was won by [[Germans|German]] Long Track specialist [[Gerd Riss]] (the 1991 [[Individual Speedway Long Track World Championship|Long Track World Champion]], Riss would go on to win another 7 Long Track World titles in his career). The last time the track held the event was in 1995 when it was won by another Kiwi, Mark Thorpe.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Harness racing in New Zealand]]\n* [[Riccarton Racecourse]]\n* [[Alexandra Park, Auckland]]\n* [[Forbury Park Raceway]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Addington Raceway}}\n* [http://www.addington.co.nz/ Official website of the Addington Raceway]\n\n{{coord|-43.5435|172.5986|region:NZ-CAN_type:landmark|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Sports venues in Christchurch]]\n[[Category:Horse racing venues in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Harness racing in New Zealand]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Addington Raceway, 2004.jpg|thumb|Addington Raceway in 2004]]\n'''Addington Raceway''' or '''The Met''' is the home of the Metropolitan Trotting Club in [[Addington, New Zealand|Addington]], [[Christchurch]] in New Zealand.  The venue consists of a trotting track, a greyhound track, conference centre and restaurants. It is also home to many feature harness races such as: The [[New Zealand Trotting Cup]] and the [[Dominion Handicap]].\n\nThe raceway forms part of a sporting complex that includes [[Rugby League Park]] and the [[CBS Canterbury Arena]].\n\n==History==\nThe NZ Metropolitan Trotting Club (NZMTC) was first based at [[Lancaster Park]] in [[Waltham, New Zealand|Waltham]].  [[Charles Louisson]], a steward of NZMTC and [[Mayor of Christchurch]] at the time,<ref name=\"NZETC\">{{cite book|title=The Cyclopedia of New Zealand (Canterbury Provincial District)|publisher=Cyclopedia Company Limited|location=Christchurch |year=1903|chapter=The Hon. Charles Louisson |url= http://www.nzetc.org/tm/scholarly/tei-Cyc03Cycl-t1-body1-d3-d9.html |accessdate=4 November 2011}}</ref> helped to secure land in [[Addington, New Zealand|Addington]] and in 1899, the club moved to the present site.  From 1906 until his death<ref>{{cite web|title=Presidents: NZMTC |url=http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=2&ID=20 |publisher=Addington Raceway |accessdate=4 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111225183058/http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=2&ID=20 |archivedate=25 December 2011 }}</ref> in 1924, he was the president of the NZMTC.  The grounds were enlarged during his presidency.<ref name=\"Louisson Handicap\">{{cite web|title=Mescellany |url=http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=6&ItemId=398&AlphaId=12&CategoryId=3 |publisher=Addington Raceway |accessdate=4 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130207074257/http://addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=6&ItemId=398&AlphaId=12&CategoryId=3 |archivedate=7 February 2013 }}</ref>  The Louisson Handicap was an annual race that was held for many years.  Between 1914 and 1923, Louisson annually donated the silver trophy for the New Zealand Trotting Cup, which he had manufactured in England.<ref>{{cite web|title=Racing History |url=http://www.addington.co.nz/timeline.asp?Case=1&ID=1921 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060929095613/http://www.addington.co.nz/Timeline.asp?Case=1&ID=1921 |url-status=dead |archive-date=29 September 2006 |publisher=Addington Raceway |accessdate=7 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\n===Interdominions===\n\nAddington has hosted the Interdominions in 1938, 1951, 1961, 1971, 1979, 1987, 1995 and 2003. The 2011 series was planned to be at Addington but due to the 2011 Christchurch Earthquake was moved to Alexandra Park.\n\nAddington Raceway has also hosted the New Zealand Long Track Grand Prix for [[Motorcycle speedway]]. It first hosted the GP in 1991 and was won by Kiwi rider [[Mitch Shirra]]. It held the event again in 1992 when it was won by [[Germans|German]] Long Track specialist [[Gerd Riss]] (the 1991 [[Individual Speedway Long Track World Championship|Long Track World Champion]], Riss would go on to win another 7 Long Track World titles in his career). The last time the track held the event was in 1995 when it was won by another Kiwi, Mark Thorpe.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Harness racing in New Zealand]]\n* [[Riccarton Racecourse]]\n* [[Alexandra Park, Auckland]]\n* [[Forbury Park Raceway]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Addington Raceway}}\n* [http://www.addington.co.nz/ Official website of the Addington Raceway]\n\n{{coord|-43.5435|172.5986|region:NZ-CAN_type:landmark|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Sports venues in Christchurch]]\n[[Category:Horse racing venues in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Harness racing in New Zealand]]\n", "name_user": "ToddyOC", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInterdominions", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addington_Raceway"}
{"title_page": "Paulina Vega", "text_new": "{{short description|Colombian model, presenter, and beauty queen}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Spanish name|Vega|Dieppa}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name = Paulina Vega \n| image =Paulina Vega en la XXXVI versi\u00f3n de la Caminata de la Solidaridad por Colombia.jpg\n| birth_name = Paulina Vega Dieppa\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|1|15}} \n| birth_place = [[Barranquilla]], [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Atl\u00e1ntico]], [[Colombia]]\n| residence = \n| height = {{height|m=1.76}}\n| measurements = \n| hair_color = [[Brown hair|Brown]]\n| eye_color = [[Eye color#Brown|Brown]] \n| title =[[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico 2013]]<br>[[Miss Colombia 2013]]<br>[[Miss Universe 2014]]\n| competitions = [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico 2013]]<br>(Winner)<br>[[Miss Colombia 2013]]<br>(Winner)<br>[[Miss Universe 2014]]<br>(Winner)\n}}\n[[File:UNI2014 08882.jpg|thumb]]\n'''Paulina Vega Dieppa''' ({{IPA-es|paw\u02c8lina \u02c8\u03b2e\u0263a}}; born 15 January 1993) is a Colombian TV Host, model and beauty queen who was crowned [[Miss Colombia 2013]] and [[Miss Universe 2014]]. Vega is the second [[Miss Universe]] from [[Colombia]].\n\n==Early life==\nVega was born in [[Barranquilla]], Colombia to [[cardiologist]] Rodolfo Vega Llama and Laura Dieppa and has seven brothers and sisters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/miss-colombia-miss-universe-winner-paulina-vega-and-colombias-murky-culture-of-ott-beauty-pageants-10002895.html|title=Paulina Vega wins Miss Universe - here's why Colombian pageants are controversial|work=The Independent|access-date=2018-07-29|language=en-GB}}</ref>  She is the granddaughter of Colombian [[tenor]] Gast\u00f3n Vega and [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico 1953]] Elvira Castillo and a distant cousin of [[Miss Colombia 2014]] [[Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez]] who placed first runner-up at [[Miss Universe 2015]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/chi-miss-universe-winner-20150125-story.html|title=Miss Colombia Paulina Vega crowned Miss Universe 2015|last=|first=|date=26 January 2015|work=Chicago Tribune|access-date=2018-07-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latinpost.com/articles/35694/20150203/miss-colombia-2014-ariadna-gutierrez-feels-perfect-despite-comments-shes.htm|title=Miss Colombia 2014 Ariadna Gutierrez Says She Feels 'Perfect' Despite Comments She's Overweight, Is Preparing for Miss Universe 2015|date=3 February 2015|website=Latin Post|accessdate=21 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Pageantry==\n\n===Miss Colombia 2013===\nVega competed in [[Miss Colombia 2013]] on November 11, 2013, held in [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]], representing the [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department]], where she won the title of Miss Colombia, gaining the right to represent the country at [[Miss Universe 2014]]. She was crowned by the outgoing titleholder [[Lucia Aldana]], [[Miss Colombia 2012]]. Vega became the eleventh Miss Atlantico to win that title since the [[Miss Colombia]] pageant began in 1934, the first Miss Atlantico to win Miss Universe, and the second Colombian to win [[Miss Universe]] after [[Luz Marina Zuluaga]] in [[Miss Universe 1958|1958]].<ref>{{cite news| author1=Associated Press|title=Miss Colombia |url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-nn-miss-universe-20150125-story.html|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Miss Universe 2014===\n[[Miss Universe 2013]], [[Gabriela Isler]] from [[Venezuela]], crowned her as Miss Universe 2014 on January 25, 2015, in [[Doral, Florida]], beating 87 contestants. She was the second Colombian in 56 years to win the Miss Universe crown after Miss Universe 1958 [[Luz Marina Zuluaga]]. Vega debuted the pageant's new crown as designed by Diamonds International Corporation, a Czech-based jeweler officially responsible for Miss Universe jewelry. Her prize package included cash, a year contract promoting Miss Universe, world travel, a rent-free luxury apartment in New York City, a gift bag stuffed with designer shoes, dresses and beauty products, a US$100,000 [[stipend]] for a two-year course at the [[New York Film Academy]], and free access to famous fashion houses and beauty parlors. Vega intends to spend her year-long reign travelling the world to lecture on [[humanitarian]] issues and to promote education regards [[HIV/AIDS]]. After her crowning, Paulina was interviewed by [[CNN en Espa\u00f1ol]], [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]], Rendezvous with Miss Universe ([[Indonesia]]), [[Fox News]], [[Univision]], [[Caracol Televisi\u00f3n]] (Colombia), [[RCN TV]] (Colombia), [[Telemundo]], ''[[Way Too Early]] with [[Thomas Roberts (television journalist)|Thomas Roberts]]'' ([[MSNBC]]), ''[[Morning Joe]]'' (MSNBC), ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today]]'' ([[NBC]]) and ''[[Live! with Kelly and Michael]]'' ([[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]).<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.missuniverse.com/news/index/year:2015/month:1#.VPzPO9LF--0 |title=Miss Universe 2014: Media Tour in America|publisher=missuniverse.com}} Retrieved January 2015</ref>\n\nIn early February, Vega attended Mercedes Benz-[[New York Fashion Week]] in New York City together with [[Miss USA 2014]] and [[Miss Teen USA 2014]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/miss-universe/photos/miss-universe-attends-new-york-fashion-week/eventshow/46299187.cms |title=Miss Universe 2014: NY Fashion Week 2015|publisher=beautypageants.indiatimes.com}} Retrieved February 2015</ref> On February 17, 2015, Vega made an appearance on the season finale of ''[[The Celebrity Apprentice]]''. On February 20, 2015, Vega visited [[Indonesia]] to attend the 19th annual [[Puteri Indonesia 2015]] pageant. She assisted in the crowning of Puteri Indonesia 2015 (Miss Universe Indonesia).<ref>{{cite web| url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-paulina-vega-was-captivated-by-indonesia/ |title=Miss Universe Paulina Vega was captivated by Indonesia |publisher=[[Pageants News]]|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref> She also visited [[Jakarta]] and [[Surabaya]] where she filmed a publicity for {{ill|YOU\u2022C1000|id|YOU C-1000}} along with former Miss Universes [[Dayana Mendoza]] and [[Olivia Culpo]] in [[Bali]].\n\nIn early March, Vega traveled to Doral, Florida, to attend the [[World Golf Championships]] at [[Trump National Doral Miami]] golf resort. On March 8, 2015, Vega became public speaker at the [[Women's History Month]] Event 2015 in New York City. On March 11, 2015, Vega volunteered at [[Gay Men's Health Crisis|GMHC]], New York City, to learn about their services and critical issues of HIV and AIDS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aidsmap.com/org/9716/page/1868839/|title=Miss Universe 2014: Social Project in GMHC with Paulina Vega|publisher=aidsmap.com|accessdate=March 12, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402180218/http://www.aidsmap.com/org/9716/page/1868839/#|archive-date=April 2, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In addition, she was interviewed on MSNBC in ''Out There with Thomas Roberts'' to discuss how she would work to raise awareness for HIV/AIDS in her new role.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/watch/raising-awareness-and-laughs-via-celibacy-411726915985 |title=Miss Universe 2014: Raising Awareness and laughs via Celibacy, \"Out There with Thomas Robarts| publisher=www.msnbc.com| accessdate=March 11, 2015}}</ref> On March 13, 2015, she joined New York state senator [[Jose Peralta]] to help honor distinguished women in the community as a part of Women's History Month at [[Woodside, Queens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://missuniversenews.wordpress.com/2015/03/13/miss-universe-2014-paulina-vega-joins-senator-jose-peralta-to-honor-distinguished-women-in-the-community/ |title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina joins Senator Jose Peralta|publisher=www.missuniversenews.wordpress.com|accessdate=March 13, 2015}}</ref> On March 19, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Nice]], France. She was invited by {{ill|Saga France|fr|lt=SAGA Cosmetics}} to launch the 'Miss Universe Style Illuminate by CHI' haircare line.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sagacosmetics.com/actualite/gagnez-votre-voyage-a-nice-pour-rencontrer-paulina-vega,224.html|title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina visits France for SAGA Cosmetics|publisher=www.sagacosmetics.com|accessdate=March 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321003004/http://www.sagacosmetics.com/actualite/gagnez-votre-voyage-a-nice-pour-rencontrer-paulina-vega,224.html#|archive-date=March 21, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On March 22, 2015, Vega attended the [[CosmoProf]] Worldwide Beauty Show to launch the 'Miss Universe Style Illuminate by CHI' haircare line at [[Bologna]], Italy. During the same week, she was also invited to launch the '{{ill|Yamamay|it}} for Miss Universe' 2015 Swimwear Collection at [[Milan]]. After her European trips, Vega visited [[Toronto]], Canada, for the first time as it prepared for the [[2015 Pan American Games]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://missuniversecanada.ca/2-months-after-winning-miss-universe-colombian-paulina-vega-visits-toronto/ |title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina visits Canada |publisher=missuniversecanada.com |date= }} Retrieved March 2015</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2015, Vega attended the Jeffrey [[Fashion Cares]] 2015 at ArtBeam in New York City. On April 9, 2015, Vega emerged as the winner of Missosology's Timeless Beauty 2014 contest. On April 10, 2015, Vega attended AID FOR AIDS International to support National Youth HIV & AIDS Awareness Day. She is committed to fight against HIV and AIDS, as well as providing support to children and young adults fighting this disease.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://voxxi.com/2015/03/10/miss-universe-hiv/ |title=Miss Universe words of wisdom for Women and Girls HIV/AIDS Awareness Day |publisher=voxxi.com |accessdate=March 10, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150311223631/http://voxxi.com/2015/03/10/miss-universe-hiv/# |archive-date=March 11, 2015 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> On the same day Vega attended the Colombian International Film Festival in New York. On April 13, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Santiago]], [[Chile]], where she was invited for a photo shoot with [[S.A.C.I. Falabella|Falabella]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.sashfactor.info/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=15092&p=323545#p323545| title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina visits Chile |publisher=sashfactor.info |date= |accessdate=April 14, 2015}}</ref> On April 15, 2015, Vega became the godmother for the [[Latino Commission on AIDS]]. During the same event, she helped launching the 25th anniversary campaign at [[Macy's Herald Square]] in New York City. On April 20, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Bogot\u00e1]], [[Colombia]], where she was officially revealed as the new face of Falabella.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-2014-paulina-vega-is-the-face-of-falabella/| title=Miss Universe 2014 Paulina Vega is the face of Falabella |publisher=pageantsnews.com |date= |accessdate=April 28, 2015}}</ref> On April 27, 2015, Vega began her homecoming trip to Colombia, arriving in Bogot\u00e1. On April 28, 2015, Vega met the President of Colombia, [[Juan Manuel Santos]], and his wife [[Mar\u00eda Clemencia Rodr\u00edguez M\u00fanera|Clemencia Santos]] at the [[Casa de Nari\u00f1o|Presidential Palace]] for a welcoming ceremony. Vega was appointed as the ambassador to fight against [[child malnutrition]]. On April 29, 2015, Vega met the employees of Vogue Cosmetics Plant, the sponsor of Miss Universe in Colombia. She was the guest of honor at [[RCN Televisi\u00f3n|RCN TV]] where she met Colombia's first Miss Universe, [[Luz Marina Zuluaga]]. On April 30, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]] where she met the board of directors of Miss Colombia. Also on April 30, Vega traveled to her hometown, [[Barranquilla]]. On May 1, 2015, Vega attended a welcoming event at {{ill|Plaza de la Paz|es|Plaza de la Paz (Barranquilla)}} where she met the Mayor of Barranquilla, Ms. [[Elsa Noguera]].\n\nOn May 1, 2015, Vega was chosen as one of the 50 most beautiful Hispanic celebrities by ''[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]'' magazine. During the same day, Vega walked the red carpet at the ''People en Espa\u00f1ol'' 50 Most Beautiful 2015 Gala in New York City. On May 14, 2015, Vega attended the 13th Annual Smile Gala in New York City. On May 15, 2015, Vega attended the [[Latino Commission on AIDS]] Cielo in New York City. On May 18, 2015, Vega attended the 30th annual [[AIDS Walk New York]]. On May 27, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Macau]], China, to attend the grand opening of [[Galaxy Macau]] and Broadway Macau.\n\nOn June 5, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Machala]], [[Ecuador]], to attend the Annual 'Fiestas Machala' Parade. Vega received a certificate from Mayor {{ill|Carlos Falquez Aguilar|es}} and the city of Machala for her visit. Vega also met with Mayor of Guayaquil [[Jaime Nebot]] during her trip. On June 27, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Almaty]], [[Kazakhstan]], to attend the VII [[Abay Opera House|Opera]] Ball and serve as Master of Ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-2014-paulina-vega-will-visit-kazakhstan/|title=Miss Universe 2014 Paulina Vega will visit Kazakhstan  |publisher=pageantsnews.com |date= |accessdate=April 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Paulina Vega Colombia Moda.jpg|left|thumb|Paulina Vega modeling for [[Falabella]] in the [[Plaza Mayor, Medell\u00edn]]]]\nOn July 12, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]], to attend the [[Miss USA 2015|2015 Miss USA]] pageant. Vega assisted crowning the winner, [[Olivia Jordan]] of [[Oklahoma]]. On July 20, 2015, Vega attended the ''[[Pixels (2015 film)|Pixels]]'' New York premiere.<ref>{{cite web|title = \"Miss Universe 2014 Paulina Vega attends the Pixels\"|url = http://gettyimages.com/...paulina-vega-attends-the-pixels.../481290388|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 28, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On July 23, 2015, Vega volunteered at [[Gay Men's Health Crisis]] serving meals to men and women living with HIV and AIDS.<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe Volunteer Day at GMHC|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/3858|publisher = miss universe|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On July 27, 2015, Vega participated in the Colombian Day parade in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe -Paulina Vega participated in the Colombian..|url = http://facebook.com/MissUniverse/posts/10153579081494047|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On July 28, 2015, Vega modeled for the pasarela Falabella Colombia moda 2015, in [[Medell\u00edn]], Colombia.<ref>{{cite web|title = Falabella Fashion Show \u2013 Miss Universe|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/3862|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn August 4, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Mumbai]], [[India]], to launch the Jealous 21 Limited Edition Miss Universe Collection.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega launches Jealous 21 Limited Edition Miss Universe|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/paulina-vega/482944930|publisher = getty images|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On August 22, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Nassau, Bahamas]], to attend [[Miss Teen USA 2015]] held at the [[Atlantis Paradise Island]]. Vega assisted crowning the winner [[Katherine Haik]] of [[Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite web|title = \"Katherine Haik was crowned Miss Teen USA 2015\"|url = http://pageantsnews.com/katherine-haik-was-crowned-miss-teen-usa-2015/|publisher = pageantsnews|accessdate = August 26, 2015|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150825054136/http://pageantsnews.com/katherine-haik-was-crowned-miss-teen-usa-2015/|archivedate = August 25, 2015|df = mdy-all}}</ref> On August 25, 2015, Vega attended the [[New York Yankees]] vs [[Houston Astros]] game at [[Yankee Stadium]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = \"Miss USA 2015 Olivia Jordan, Miss Universe Paulina Vega\"|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/paulina-vega/485219498|publisher = getty images|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On August 26, 2015, Vega spent a day volunteering with [[God's Love We Deliver]], helping to prepare meals in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Volunteer Day-Miss Universe|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/gallery_id:0|publisher = miss universe|accessdate = August 28, 2015}}</ref> On August 27, 2015, Vega attended the [[Ride of Fame]] city sightseeing cruise to the [[Statue of Liberty]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe Paulina Vega attend the Ride of Fame..|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news...paulina-vega-attend.../485410860|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 8, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn early September 2015, Vega attended the [[2015 US Open (tennis)|U.S. Open]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Photos-Miss Universe|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/gallery_category_id:all?year:all|publisher = miss universe|accessdate = September 9, 2015}}</ref> On September 8, 2015, Vega attended the [[Colombia]] vs [[Peru]] international [[exhibition game|friendly match]] at [[Red Bull Arena (New Jersey)|Red Bull Arena]] in [[Harrison, New Jersey]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe Paulina Vega attends the ...|url = http://gettyimages.com/...paulina-vega-attends...colombia-vs.../487344768|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 28, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> From September 10 to 16, 2015, Vega attended Spring 2016 [[New York Fashion Week]]. Among others, she attended [[\u00c1ngel S\u00e1nchez (fashion designer)|Angel Sanchez]] Show, Concept Korea Show, [[Axe (brand)|Axe]] and [[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] Show, [[Zang Toi]] Show, [[Nicholas K (designer)|Nicholas K]] Show.<ref>{{cite web|title = Nicholas K Front Row...|url = http://zimbio.com/.../Nicholas+K+Front+Row+Spring+2016+New+York|publisher = zimbio|accessdate = September 10, 2015}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Vega also attended Shenzhen Show, [[Sherri Hill]] Show and the Australian Evening & Bridal Wear Show.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega Pictures|url = http://zimbio.com/pictures/e6gbgCH3_OX/...Spring/.../Paulina+Vega|publisher = zimbio|accessdate = September 10, 2015}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On September 11, 2015, Vega attended Annual Charity Day hosted by [[Cantor Fitzgerald]] and [[BGC Partners|BGC]] at BGC Partners, INC in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega attends Annual Charity Day|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news.../paulina-vega...cantor.../487757620|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 11, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title = \" Miss Universe 2014, Paulina Vega attends the 2015 South-South...\"|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/...paulina-vega...2015-south.../490200038|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 27, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On September 28, 2015, Vega attended the Fashion 4 Development's 5th annual Official First Ladies luncheon at [[The Pierre Hotel]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega Pictures-Fashion 4 Development's 5th Annual Official...|url = http://zimbio.com/pictures/.../Fashion+4+Development.../Paulina+Vega|publisher = zimbio|accessdate = September 28, 2015}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> It was also around this time during her reign [[Donald Trump]] acquired full ownership of the [[Miss Universe Organization]] and sold the entire company, ending his affiliation with the pageant.\n\nOn October 11, 2015, Vega led the annual [[National Hispanic Heritage Month|Hispanic Day]] Parade up [[Fifth Avenue]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite news|title =  Hispanic Day Parade highlights Heritage Month|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/latino/hispanic-day-parade-highlights-heritage-month-article-1.2390753|newspaper = New York Daily News|accessdate = October 11, 2015}}</ref> From October 14 to 17, 2015, Vega attended various events in [[Colombia]], among them, Miss Universe Cover Party Latino Show Magazine 2015 in [[Medellin]] and [[Pereira, Colombia|Pereira]]. On October 23, 2015, Vega attended the 11th Annual [[Orphaned Starfish Foundation|Orphaned Starfish Foundation's]] New York Gala at [[55 Wall Street|Cipriani Wall Street]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Miss Universe 2014, Paulina Vega attends the 11th Annual Orphaned Starfish Foundation Gala\"|url=http://gettyimages.com/detail/news...paulina-vega-attends.../494011760|publisher=getty images.com|accessdate=October 24, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn November 3, 2015, Vega attended the 2015 Aid for AIDS Gala at [[Cipriani Downtown]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aid for AIDS Gala|url=http://gettyimages.ie/detail/news-photo/courage...and.../495718978|accessdate=November 5, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On November 16, 2015, Vega attended the [[Miss Colombia 2015|2015 Miss Colombia]] pageant in [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]], Colombia.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega sera presentadora en la elecci\u00f3n de se\u00f1orita Colombia|url = http://www.elheraldo.co/tendencias/paulina-vega-sera-presentadora-en-la-eleccion-de-senorita-colombia-228290|accessdate = November 16, 2015}}</ref> On November 18, 2015, Vega attended the 2015 [[Latin Recording Academy Person of the Year|Latin GRAMMY Person of the Year]] honoring [[Roberto Carlos (singer)|Roberto Carlos]] at the [[Mandalay Bay Events Center]] in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Latin GRAMMY Person of the Year Honoring Roberto Carlos|url=http://gettyimages.com/...paulina-vega-attends...latin-gram...|publisher=Getty images|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn December 8, 2015, Vega and the 2015 Miss Universe contestants attended a Welcome Event at [[Planet Hollywood Las Vegas|Planet Hollywood]] in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title=\"MU2015: Welcome Event at Planet Hollywood\"|url=http://globalbeauties.com/.../2015/.../mu2015-welcome-event-at-planet|publisher=global beauties|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On December 10, 2015, Vega and the 2015 Miss Universe contestants participated in the traditional National Gift Auction held at the Opportunity Village in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title=National Gift Auction Miss Universe|url=http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/gallery_id:3|publisher=miss universe|accessdate=December 13, 2015}}</ref> On December 20, 2015, Vega crowned her successor [[Pia Wurtzbach]] at Planet Hollywood in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title= \"Miss Universe2015\"|url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-2015-date-and-venue|publisher=pageants news|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuring her reign as Miss Universe, Vega traveled to [[The Bahamas]], [[Canada]], [[Chile]], [[China]], [[Colombia]], [[Kazakhstan]],<ref>{{cite web |first=Aizhan |last=Tugelbayeva |website=Tengri News |url=https://en.tengrinews.kz/show_and_style/Paulina-Vega-tells-about-her-trip-to-Kazakhstan-in-June-261520/ |title=Paulina Vega tells about her trip to Kazakhstan in June |date=14 August 2015 |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> [[Ecuador]], [[France]], [[India]], [[Indonesia]], [[Italy]] and numerous trips around the [[United States]].\n\n==Filmography==\n===TV Shows===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#b0c4de;\n! Year || Title || Network || Notes\n|-\n| 2016-2017 || ''{{ill|A otro nivel|es}}''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caracoltv.com/a-otro-nivel/paulina-vega|title=Paulina Vega|website=www.caracoltv.com|access-date=March 30, 2016|editor=[[Caracol Televisi\u00f3n]]}}</ref> || [[Caracol Televisi\u00f3n|Caracol TV]] || Host\n|-\n| 2019 || {{ill|2019 Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival|es|LX Festival Internacional de la Canci\u00f3n de Vi\u00f1a del Mar|lt=2019}} [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival]] Opening || [[Fox Channel (Latin America)|Fox Channel]] || Host\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Colombia|Biography}}\n{{commonscat}}\n* [http://www.paulinavega.com/ Official Paulina Vega website]\n* [http://www.srtacolombia.org/ Official Miss Colombia website] {{in lang|es}}\n* [http://www.missuniverse.com/members/profile/661314 Profile in Miss Universe]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{S-bef|before={{flagicon|Venezuela}} [[Gabriela Isler]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Miss Universe]]\n|years=[[Miss Universe 2014|2014]]}}\n{{S-aft|after={{flagicon|Philippines}} [[Pia Wurtzbach]]}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[File:Flag of Valle del Cauca.svg|border|22x20px|Valle]] [[Lucia Aldana]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Miss Colombia]]\n|years=2013}}\n{{S-aft|after={{nowrap|[[File:Flag of Sucre (Colombia).svg|border|22x20px|Sucre]] [[Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez]]}}}}\n{{S-bef|before=Yuliana Mej\u00eda}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico]]\n|years=2013}}\n{{S-aft|after=Mayra Le\u00f3n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Miss Universe 2014 delegates}}\n{{Miss Universe titleholders}}\n{{Miss Colombia winners in the Big Four pageants}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vega, Paulina}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Miss Universe 2014 contestants]]\n[[Category:Miss Colombia winners]]\n[[Category:Miss Universe winners]]\n[[Category:People from Barranquilla]]\n[[Category:Colombian female models]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Colombian model, presenter, and beauty queen}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Spanish name|Vega|Dieppa}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name = Paulina Vega \n| image =Paulina Vega en la XXXVI versi\u00f3n de la Caminata de la Solidaridad por Colombia.jpg\n| birth_name = Paulina Vega Dieppa\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|1|15}} \n| birth_place = [[Barranquilla]], [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Atl\u00e1ntico]], [[Colombia]]\n| residence = \n| height = {{height|m=1.76}}\n| measurements = \n| hair_color = [[Brown hair|Brown]]\n| eye_color = [[Eye color#Brown|Brown]] \n| title =[[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico 2013]]<br>[[Miss Colombia 2013]]<br>[[Miss Universe 2014]]\n| competitions = [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico 2013]]<br>(Winner)<br>[[Miss Colombia 2013]]<br>(Winner)<br>[[Miss Universe 2014]]<br>(Winner)\n}}\n[[File:UNI2014 08882.jpg|thumb]]\n'''Paulina Vega Dieppa''' ({{IPA-es|pau\u02c8lina \u02c8\u03b2e\u0263a}}; born 15 January 1993) is a Colombian TV Host, model and beauty queen who was crowned [[Miss Colombia 2013]] and [[Miss Universe 2014]]. Vega is the second [[Miss Universe]] from [[Colombia]].\n\n==Early life==\nVega was born in [[Barranquilla]], Colombia to [[cardiologist]] Rodolfo Vega Llama and Laura Dieppa and has seven brothers and sisters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/miss-colombia-miss-universe-winner-paulina-vega-and-colombias-murky-culture-of-ott-beauty-pageants-10002895.html|title=Paulina Vega wins Miss Universe - here's why Colombian pageants are controversial|work=The Independent|access-date=2018-07-29|language=en-GB}}</ref>  She is the granddaughter of Colombian [[tenor]] Gast\u00f3n Vega and [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico 1953]] Elvira Castillo and a distant cousin of [[Miss Colombia 2014]] [[Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez]] who placed first runner-up at [[Miss Universe 2015]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/chi-miss-universe-winner-20150125-story.html|title=Miss Colombia Paulina Vega crowned Miss Universe 2015|last=|first=|date=26 January 2015|work=Chicago Tribune|access-date=2018-07-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latinpost.com/articles/35694/20150203/miss-colombia-2014-ariadna-gutierrez-feels-perfect-despite-comments-shes.htm|title=Miss Colombia 2014 Ariadna Gutierrez Says She Feels 'Perfect' Despite Comments She's Overweight, Is Preparing for Miss Universe 2015|date=3 February 2015|website=Latin Post|accessdate=21 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Pageantry==\n\n===Miss Colombia 2013===\nVega competed in [[Miss Colombia 2013]] on November 11, 2013, held in [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]], representing the [[Atl\u00e1ntico Department]], where she won the title of Miss Colombia, gaining the right to represent the country at [[Miss Universe 2014]]. She was crowned by the outgoing titleholder [[Lucia Aldana]], [[Miss Colombia 2012]]. Vega became the eleventh Miss Atlantico to win that title since the [[Miss Colombia]] pageant began in 1934, the first Miss Atlantico to win Miss Universe, and the second Colombian to win [[Miss Universe]] after [[Luz Marina Zuluaga]] in [[Miss Universe 1958|1958]].<ref>{{cite news| author1=Associated Press|title=Miss Colombia |url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-nn-miss-universe-20150125-story.html|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Miss Universe 2014===\n[[Miss Universe 2013]], [[Gabriela Isler]] from [[Venezuela]], crowned her as Miss Universe 2014 on January 25, 2015, in [[Doral, Florida]], beating 87 contestants. She was the second Colombian in 56 years to win the Miss Universe crown after Miss Universe 1958 [[Luz Marina Zuluaga]]. Vega debuted the pageant's new crown as designed by Diamonds International Corporation, a Czech-based jeweler officially responsible for Miss Universe jewelry. Her prize package included cash, a year contract promoting Miss Universe, world travel, a rent-free luxury apartment in New York City, a gift bag stuffed with designer shoes, dresses and beauty products, a US$100,000 [[stipend]] for a two-year course at the [[New York Film Academy]], and free access to famous fashion houses and beauty parlors. Vega intends to spend her year-long reign travelling the world to lecture on [[humanitarian]] issues and to promote education regards [[HIV/AIDS]]. After her crowning, Paulina was interviewed by [[CNN en Espa\u00f1ol]], [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]], Rendezvous with Miss Universe ([[Indonesia]]), [[Fox News]], [[Univision]], [[Caracol Televisi\u00f3n]] (Colombia), [[RCN TV]] (Colombia), [[Telemundo]], ''[[Way Too Early]] with [[Thomas Roberts (television journalist)|Thomas Roberts]]'' ([[MSNBC]]), ''[[Morning Joe]]'' (MSNBC), ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today]]'' ([[NBC]]) and ''[[Live! with Kelly and Michael]]'' ([[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]).<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.missuniverse.com/news/index/year:2015/month:1#.VPzPO9LF--0 |title=Miss Universe 2014: Media Tour in America|publisher=missuniverse.com}} Retrieved January 2015</ref>\n\nIn early February, Vega attended Mercedes Benz-[[New York Fashion Week]] in New York City together with [[Miss USA 2014]] and [[Miss Teen USA 2014]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/miss-universe/photos/miss-universe-attends-new-york-fashion-week/eventshow/46299187.cms |title=Miss Universe 2014: NY Fashion Week 2015|publisher=beautypageants.indiatimes.com}} Retrieved February 2015</ref> On February 17, 2015, Vega made an appearance on the season finale of ''[[The Celebrity Apprentice]]''. On February 20, 2015, Vega visited [[Indonesia]] to attend the 19th annual [[Puteri Indonesia 2015]] pageant. She assisted in the crowning of Puteri Indonesia 2015 (Miss Universe Indonesia).<ref>{{cite web| url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-paulina-vega-was-captivated-by-indonesia/ |title=Miss Universe Paulina Vega was captivated by Indonesia |publisher=[[Pageants News]]|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref> She also visited [[Jakarta]] and [[Surabaya]] where she filmed a publicity for {{ill|YOU\u2022C1000|id|YOU C-1000}} along with former Miss Universes [[Dayana Mendoza]] and [[Olivia Culpo]] in [[Bali]].\n\nIn early March, Vega traveled to Doral, Florida, to attend the [[World Golf Championships]] at [[Trump National Doral Miami]] golf resort. On March 8, 2015, Vega became public speaker at the [[Women's History Month]] Event 2015 in New York City. On March 11, 2015, Vega volunteered at [[Gay Men's Health Crisis|GMHC]], New York City, to learn about their services and critical issues of HIV and AIDS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aidsmap.com/org/9716/page/1868839/|title=Miss Universe 2014: Social Project in GMHC with Paulina Vega|publisher=aidsmap.com|accessdate=March 12, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402180218/http://www.aidsmap.com/org/9716/page/1868839/#|archive-date=April 2, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In addition, she was interviewed on MSNBC in ''Out There with Thomas Roberts'' to discuss how she would work to raise awareness for HIV/AIDS in her new role.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/watch/raising-awareness-and-laughs-via-celibacy-411726915985 |title=Miss Universe 2014: Raising Awareness and laughs via Celibacy, \"Out There with Thomas Robarts| publisher=www.msnbc.com| accessdate=March 11, 2015}}</ref> On March 13, 2015, she joined New York state senator [[Jose Peralta]] to help honor distinguished women in the community as a part of Women's History Month at [[Woodside, Queens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://missuniversenews.wordpress.com/2015/03/13/miss-universe-2014-paulina-vega-joins-senator-jose-peralta-to-honor-distinguished-women-in-the-community/ |title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina joins Senator Jose Peralta|publisher=www.missuniversenews.wordpress.com|accessdate=March 13, 2015}}</ref> On March 19, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Nice]], France. She was invited by {{ill|Saga France|fr|lt=SAGA Cosmetics}} to launch the 'Miss Universe Style Illuminate by CHI' haircare line.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sagacosmetics.com/actualite/gagnez-votre-voyage-a-nice-pour-rencontrer-paulina-vega,224.html|title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina visits France for SAGA Cosmetics|publisher=www.sagacosmetics.com|accessdate=March 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321003004/http://www.sagacosmetics.com/actualite/gagnez-votre-voyage-a-nice-pour-rencontrer-paulina-vega,224.html#|archive-date=March 21, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On March 22, 2015, Vega attended the [[CosmoProf]] Worldwide Beauty Show to launch the 'Miss Universe Style Illuminate by CHI' haircare line at [[Bologna]], Italy. During the same week, she was also invited to launch the '{{ill|Yamamay|it}} for Miss Universe' 2015 Swimwear Collection at [[Milan]]. After her European trips, Vega visited [[Toronto]], Canada, for the first time as it prepared for the [[2015 Pan American Games]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://missuniversecanada.ca/2-months-after-winning-miss-universe-colombian-paulina-vega-visits-toronto/ |title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina visits Canada |publisher=missuniversecanada.com |date= }} Retrieved March 2015</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2015, Vega attended the Jeffrey [[Fashion Cares]] 2015 at ArtBeam in New York City. On April 9, 2015, Vega emerged as the winner of Missosology's Timeless Beauty 2014 contest. On April 10, 2015, Vega attended AID FOR AIDS International to support National Youth HIV & AIDS Awareness Day. She is committed to fight against HIV and AIDS, as well as providing support to children and young adults fighting this disease.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://voxxi.com/2015/03/10/miss-universe-hiv/ |title=Miss Universe words of wisdom for Women and Girls HIV/AIDS Awareness Day |publisher=voxxi.com |accessdate=March 10, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150311223631/http://voxxi.com/2015/03/10/miss-universe-hiv/# |archive-date=March 11, 2015 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> On the same day Vega attended the Colombian International Film Festival in New York. On April 13, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Santiago]], [[Chile]], where she was invited for a photo shoot with [[S.A.C.I. Falabella|Falabella]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.sashfactor.info/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=15092&p=323545#p323545| title=Miss Universe 2014: Paulina visits Chile |publisher=sashfactor.info |date= |accessdate=April 14, 2015}}</ref> On April 15, 2015, Vega became the godmother for the [[Latino Commission on AIDS]]. During the same event, she helped launching the 25th anniversary campaign at [[Macy's Herald Square]] in New York City. On April 20, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Bogot\u00e1]], [[Colombia]], where she was officially revealed as the new face of Falabella.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-2014-paulina-vega-is-the-face-of-falabella/| title=Miss Universe 2014 Paulina Vega is the face of Falabella |publisher=pageantsnews.com |date= |accessdate=April 28, 2015}}</ref> On April 27, 2015, Vega began her homecoming trip to Colombia, arriving in Bogot\u00e1. On April 28, 2015, Vega met the President of Colombia, [[Juan Manuel Santos]], and his wife [[Mar\u00eda Clemencia Rodr\u00edguez M\u00fanera|Clemencia Santos]] at the [[Casa de Nari\u00f1o|Presidential Palace]] for a welcoming ceremony. Vega was appointed as the ambassador to fight against [[child malnutrition]]. On April 29, 2015, Vega met the employees of Vogue Cosmetics Plant, the sponsor of Miss Universe in Colombia. She was the guest of honor at [[RCN Televisi\u00f3n|RCN TV]] where she met Colombia's first Miss Universe, [[Luz Marina Zuluaga]]. On April 30, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]] where she met the board of directors of Miss Colombia. Also on April 30, Vega traveled to her hometown, [[Barranquilla]]. On May 1, 2015, Vega attended a welcoming event at {{ill|Plaza de la Paz|es|Plaza de la Paz (Barranquilla)}} where she met the Mayor of Barranquilla, Ms. [[Elsa Noguera]].\n\nOn May 1, 2015, Vega was chosen as one of the 50 most beautiful Hispanic celebrities by ''[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]'' magazine. During the same day, Vega walked the red carpet at the ''People en Espa\u00f1ol'' 50 Most Beautiful 2015 Gala in New York City. On May 14, 2015, Vega attended the 13th Annual Smile Gala in New York City. On May 15, 2015, Vega attended the [[Latino Commission on AIDS]] Cielo in New York City. On May 18, 2015, Vega attended the 30th annual [[AIDS Walk New York]]. On May 27, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Macau]], China, to attend the grand opening of [[Galaxy Macau]] and Broadway Macau.\n\nOn June 5, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Machala]], [[Ecuador]], to attend the Annual 'Fiestas Machala' Parade. Vega received a certificate from Mayor {{ill|Carlos Falquez Aguilar|es}} and the city of Machala for her visit. Vega also met with Mayor of Guayaquil [[Jaime Nebot]] during her trip. On June 27, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Almaty]], [[Kazakhstan]], to attend the VII [[Abay Opera House|Opera]] Ball and serve as Master of Ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-2014-paulina-vega-will-visit-kazakhstan/|title=Miss Universe 2014 Paulina Vega will visit Kazakhstan  |publisher=pageantsnews.com |date= |accessdate=April 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Paulina Vega Colombia Moda.jpg|left|thumb|Paulina Vega modeling for [[Falabella]] in the [[Plaza Mayor, Medell\u00edn]]]]\nOn July 12, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]], to attend the [[Miss USA 2015|2015 Miss USA]] pageant. Vega assisted crowning the winner, [[Olivia Jordan]] of [[Oklahoma]]. On July 20, 2015, Vega attended the ''[[Pixels (2015 film)|Pixels]]'' New York premiere.<ref>{{cite web|title = \"Miss Universe 2014 Paulina Vega attends the Pixels\"|url = http://gettyimages.com/...paulina-vega-attends-the-pixels.../481290388|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 28, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On July 23, 2015, Vega volunteered at [[Gay Men's Health Crisis]] serving meals to men and women living with HIV and AIDS.<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe Volunteer Day at GMHC|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/3858|publisher = miss universe|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On July 27, 2015, Vega participated in the Colombian Day parade in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe -Paulina Vega participated in the Colombian..|url = http://facebook.com/MissUniverse/posts/10153579081494047|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On July 28, 2015, Vega modeled for the pasarela Falabella Colombia moda 2015, in [[Medell\u00edn]], Colombia.<ref>{{cite web|title = Falabella Fashion Show \u2013 Miss Universe|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/3862|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn August 4, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Mumbai]], [[India]], to launch the Jealous 21 Limited Edition Miss Universe Collection.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega launches Jealous 21 Limited Edition Miss Universe|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/paulina-vega/482944930|publisher = getty images|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On August 22, 2015, Vega traveled to [[Nassau, Bahamas]], to attend [[Miss Teen USA 2015]] held at the [[Atlantis Paradise Island]]. Vega assisted crowning the winner [[Katherine Haik]] of [[Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite web|title = \"Katherine Haik was crowned Miss Teen USA 2015\"|url = http://pageantsnews.com/katherine-haik-was-crowned-miss-teen-usa-2015/|publisher = pageantsnews|accessdate = August 26, 2015|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150825054136/http://pageantsnews.com/katherine-haik-was-crowned-miss-teen-usa-2015/|archivedate = August 25, 2015|df = mdy-all}}</ref> On August 25, 2015, Vega attended the [[New York Yankees]] vs [[Houston Astros]] game at [[Yankee Stadium]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = \"Miss USA 2015 Olivia Jordan, Miss Universe Paulina Vega\"|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/paulina-vega/485219498|publisher = getty images|accessdate = August 26, 2015}}</ref> On August 26, 2015, Vega spent a day volunteering with [[God's Love We Deliver]], helping to prepare meals in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Volunteer Day-Miss Universe|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/gallery_id:0|publisher = miss universe|accessdate = August 28, 2015}}</ref> On August 27, 2015, Vega attended the [[Ride of Fame]] city sightseeing cruise to the [[Statue of Liberty]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe Paulina Vega attend the Ride of Fame..|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news...paulina-vega-attend.../485410860|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 8, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn early September 2015, Vega attended the [[2015 US Open (tennis)|U.S. Open]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Photos-Miss Universe|url = http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/gallery_category_id:all?year:all|publisher = miss universe|accessdate = September 9, 2015}}</ref> On September 8, 2015, Vega attended the [[Colombia]] vs [[Peru]] international [[exhibition game|friendly match]] at [[Red Bull Arena (New Jersey)|Red Bull Arena]] in [[Harrison, New Jersey]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Miss Universe Paulina Vega attends the ...|url = http://gettyimages.com/...paulina-vega-attends...colombia-vs.../487344768|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 28, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> From September 10 to 16, 2015, Vega attended Spring 2016 [[New York Fashion Week]]. Among others, she attended [[\u00c1ngel S\u00e1nchez (fashion designer)|Angel Sanchez]] Show, Concept Korea Show, [[Axe (brand)|Axe]] and [[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] Show, [[Zang Toi]] Show, [[Nicholas K (designer)|Nicholas K]] Show.<ref>{{cite web|title = Nicholas K Front Row...|url = http://zimbio.com/.../Nicholas+K+Front+Row+Spring+2016+New+York|publisher = zimbio|accessdate = September 10, 2015}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Vega also attended Shenzhen Show, [[Sherri Hill]] Show and the Australian Evening & Bridal Wear Show.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega Pictures|url = http://zimbio.com/pictures/e6gbgCH3_OX/...Spring/.../Paulina+Vega|publisher = zimbio|accessdate = September 10, 2015}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On September 11, 2015, Vega attended Annual Charity Day hosted by [[Cantor Fitzgerald]] and [[BGC Partners|BGC]] at BGC Partners, INC in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega attends Annual Charity Day|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/news.../paulina-vega...cantor.../487757620|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 11, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title = \" Miss Universe 2014, Paulina Vega attends the 2015 South-South...\"|url = http://gettyimages.com/detail/...paulina-vega...2015-south.../490200038|publisher = getty images|accessdate = September 27, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On September 28, 2015, Vega attended the Fashion 4 Development's 5th annual Official First Ladies luncheon at [[The Pierre Hotel]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega Pictures-Fashion 4 Development's 5th Annual Official...|url = http://zimbio.com/pictures/.../Fashion+4+Development.../Paulina+Vega|publisher = zimbio|accessdate = September 28, 2015}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> It was also around this time during her reign [[Donald Trump]] acquired full ownership of the [[Miss Universe Organization]] and sold the entire company, ending his affiliation with the pageant.\n\nOn October 11, 2015, Vega led the annual [[National Hispanic Heritage Month|Hispanic Day]] Parade up [[Fifth Avenue]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite news|title =  Hispanic Day Parade highlights Heritage Month|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/latino/hispanic-day-parade-highlights-heritage-month-article-1.2390753|newspaper = New York Daily News|accessdate = October 11, 2015}}</ref> From October 14 to 17, 2015, Vega attended various events in [[Colombia]], among them, Miss Universe Cover Party Latino Show Magazine 2015 in [[Medellin]] and [[Pereira, Colombia|Pereira]]. On October 23, 2015, Vega attended the 11th Annual [[Orphaned Starfish Foundation|Orphaned Starfish Foundation's]] New York Gala at [[55 Wall Street|Cipriani Wall Street]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Miss Universe 2014, Paulina Vega attends the 11th Annual Orphaned Starfish Foundation Gala\"|url=http://gettyimages.com/detail/news...paulina-vega-attends.../494011760|publisher=getty images.com|accessdate=October 24, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn November 3, 2015, Vega attended the 2015 Aid for AIDS Gala at [[Cipriani Downtown]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aid for AIDS Gala|url=http://gettyimages.ie/detail/news-photo/courage...and.../495718978|accessdate=November 5, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On November 16, 2015, Vega attended the [[Miss Colombia 2015|2015 Miss Colombia]] pageant in [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]], Colombia.<ref>{{cite web|title = Paulina Vega sera presentadora en la elecci\u00f3n de se\u00f1orita Colombia|url = http://www.elheraldo.co/tendencias/paulina-vega-sera-presentadora-en-la-eleccion-de-senorita-colombia-228290|accessdate = November 16, 2015}}</ref> On November 18, 2015, Vega attended the 2015 [[Latin Recording Academy Person of the Year|Latin GRAMMY Person of the Year]] honoring [[Roberto Carlos (singer)|Roberto Carlos]] at the [[Mandalay Bay Events Center]] in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Latin GRAMMY Person of the Year Honoring Roberto Carlos|url=http://gettyimages.com/...paulina-vega-attends...latin-gram...|publisher=Getty images|accessdate=November 19, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn December 8, 2015, Vega and the 2015 Miss Universe contestants attended a Welcome Event at [[Planet Hollywood Las Vegas|Planet Hollywood]] in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title=\"MU2015: Welcome Event at Planet Hollywood\"|url=http://globalbeauties.com/.../2015/.../mu2015-welcome-event-at-planet|publisher=global beauties|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On December 10, 2015, Vega and the 2015 Miss Universe contestants participated in the traditional National Gift Auction held at the Opportunity Village in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title=National Gift Auction Miss Universe|url=http://missuniverse.com/photos/index/gallery_id:3|publisher=miss universe|accessdate=December 13, 2015}}</ref> On December 20, 2015, Vega crowned her successor [[Pia Wurtzbach]] at Planet Hollywood in [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|title= \"Miss Universe2015\"|url=http://pageantsnews.com/miss-universe-2015-date-and-venue|publisher=pageants news|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuring her reign as Miss Universe, Vega traveled to [[The Bahamas]], [[Canada]], [[Chile]], [[China]], [[Colombia]], [[Kazakhstan]],<ref>{{cite web |first=Aizhan |last=Tugelbayeva |website=Tengri News |url=https://en.tengrinews.kz/show_and_style/Paulina-Vega-tells-about-her-trip-to-Kazakhstan-in-June-261520/ |title=Paulina Vega tells about her trip to Kazakhstan in June |date=14 August 2015 |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> [[Ecuador]], [[France]], [[India]], [[Indonesia]], [[Italy]] and numerous trips around the [[United States]].\n\n==Filmography==\n===TV Shows===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#b0c4de;\n! Year || Title || Network || Notes\n|-\n| 2016-2017 || ''{{ill|A otro nivel|es}}''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caracoltv.com/a-otro-nivel/paulina-vega|title=Paulina Vega|website=www.caracoltv.com|access-date=March 30, 2016|editor=[[Caracol Televisi\u00f3n]]}}</ref> || [[Caracol Televisi\u00f3n|Caracol TV]] || Host\n|-\n| 2019 || {{ill|2019 Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival|es|LX Festival Internacional de la Canci\u00f3n de Vi\u00f1a del Mar|lt=2019}} [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar International Song Festival]] Opening || [[Fox Channel (Latin America)|Fox Channel]] || Host\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Colombia|Biography}}\n{{commonscat}}\n* [http://www.paulinavega.com/ Official Paulina Vega website]\n* [http://www.srtacolombia.org/ Official Miss Colombia website] {{in lang|es}}\n* [http://www.missuniverse.com/members/profile/661314 Profile in Miss Universe]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{S-bef|before={{flagicon|Venezuela}} [[Gabriela Isler]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Miss Universe]]\n|years=[[Miss Universe 2014|2014]]}}\n{{S-aft|after={{flagicon|Philippines}} [[Pia Wurtzbach]]}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[File:Flag of Valle del Cauca.svg|border|22x20px|Valle]] [[Lucia Aldana]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Miss Colombia]]\n|years=2013}}\n{{S-aft|after={{nowrap|[[File:Flag of Sucre (Colombia).svg|border|22x20px|Sucre]] [[Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez]]}}}}\n{{S-bef|before=Yuliana Mej\u00eda}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Miss Atl\u00e1ntico]]\n|years=2013}}\n{{S-aft|after=Mayra Le\u00f3n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Miss Universe 2014 delegates}}\n{{Miss Universe titleholders}}\n{{Miss Colombia winners in the Big Four pageants}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vega, Paulina}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Miss Universe 2014 contestants]]\n[[Category:Miss Colombia winners]]\n[[Category:Miss Universe winners]]\n[[Category:People from Barranquilla]]\n[[Category:Colombian female models]]\n", "name_user": "Nardog", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:fixingSpanish IPAperdiscussion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paulina_Vega"}
{"title_page": "Head & Shoulders", "text_new": "{{About|a brand of shampoo|the body parts of the same name|Head|and|Shoulder|other uses|Head and shoulders (disambiguation){{!}}Head and shoulders}}\n{{Infobox Brand\n| name                   = Head & Shoulders\n| logo                   = Head_and_shoulders.png\n| type                   = Anti-[[dandruff]], non-[[dandruff]] shampoo\n| currentowner           = {{flagicon|United States}} [[Procter & Gamble]] \n| producedby             = {{flagicon|United States}} [[Vicks|Richardson Vicks]]<br>{{flagicon|United States}} [[Procter & Gamble]]\n| origin                 = {{flagcountry|United States}}\n| introduced             = {{launch date and age|1961|1|1|df=yes}}<ref name=P&Ghist>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZyUwNAs43LcC&lpg=PA427&ots=2hUEAR_pbf&dq=william%20a%20procter%20president&pg=PA423#v=onepage&q=william%20a%20procter%20president&f=false | title=Rising Tide: Lessons from 165 Years of Brand Building at Procter and Gamble | publisher=[[Harvard Business Press]] | date=May 1, 2004 | accessdate=2013-05-07 | author=Davis, Dyer| pages=423|display-authors=etal}}</ref>, {{flagcountry|United States}}\n| markets                = [[World|Worldwide]]\n| key_people             = Claudine Marano\n| previousowners         = {{flagicon|United States}} [[Vicks|Richardson Vicks]]\n| tagline                = '''The World\u2019s No. 1 Shampoo'''\n| ambassadors            = [[Hailee Steinfeld]] and [[Kim Kardashian]] (United States)<br>[[Joe Taslim]] (Indonesia)<br>[[Blackpink]] (Korea, China, Hong Kong and Taiwan)<br>[[Iggy Azalea]] (Australia, New Zealand and United Kingdom)<br>[[Dua Lipa]] (Malaysia and Brunei)<br>[[Lady Gaga]] (Singapore and Philippines)\n| website                = {{Official|https://www.headandshoulders.com.au/en-au|Official Website English-Australia}}<br>{{Official|https://www.headandshoulders.co.uk/en-gb|Official Website English-United Kingdom}}<br>{{Official|https://www.headandshoulders.com/|Official Website English-United States}}\n}}\n'''Head & Shoulders''' ('''H&S''') [[United States|American]] [[brand]] of anti-[[dandruff]] and non-[[dandruff]] [[shampoo]] produced by parent company [[Procter & Gamble]] was introduced in [[United States]] on 1 January 1961 based in [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]] and was slogan its '''The World\u2019s No. 1 Shampoo'''.<ref name=P&Ghist2>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZyUwNAs43LcC&lpg=PA427&ots=2hUEAR_pbf&dq=william%20a%20procter%20president&pg=PA423#v=onepage&q=william%20a%20procter%20president&f=false | title=Rising Tide: Lessons from 165 Years of Brand Building at Procter and Gamble | publisher=Harvard Business Press | date=May 1, 2004 | accessdate=2013-05-07 | author=Davis, Dyer| pages=423|display-authors=etal}}</ref> \n\nIt was the \"The World's Number One Anti-[[Dandruff]] and Non-[[Dandruff]] Shampoo Brand\" of shampoo, and it was noted that \"[n]o one hair care brand gets so many ad dollars as Head & Shoulders, a twenty year old brand, and no other brand matches its sales\", despite it being a \"medicated\" shampoo.<ref>''Marketing & Decisions'' (1982), Volume 17, Issues 8-13, page 186.</ref> The brand has long been marketed under the [[tagline]], \"You Never Get a Second Chance to Make a First Impression\", which has been identified as an example of \"anxiety marketing\" commonly used by [[Procter & Gamble]] to drive sales by inducing fears of social consequences associated with the condition that the product claims to address.<ref>Thomas O'Guinn, Chris Allen, Richard J. Semenik, ''Advertising and Integrated Brand Promotion'' (2014), p. 210: \"When Head & Shoulders dandruff shampoo is advertised with the theme \"You Never Get a Second Chance to Make a First Impression\", the audience realizes that Head & Shoulders could spare them the embarrassment of having dandruff\".</ref> However, sales of the product dropped off, a phenomenon blamed on overextension of the brand into too many varieties, with over thirty kinds of Head & Shoulders being sold.<ref>Matt Haig, ''Brand Failures: The Truth about the 100 Biggest Branding Mistakes of All Time'' (2005), p. 73: \"Procter & Gamble had seen the same thing happen with its Head & Shoulders brand. Did consumers really need 31 varieties of anti-dandruff shampoo?\"</ref> \n\nThe active ingredients in Head & Shoulders are the antifungal agents [[selenium disulfide]] and [[piroctone olamine]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.headandshoulders.co.uk/en-gb/about/ingredients/our-active-ingredients |title=OUR ACTIVE INGREDIENTS |accessdate=16 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nHead & Shoulders was the #1 anti-[[dandruff]] and non-[[dandruff]] shampoo brand [[world|around the world]] with sales reaching over [[United States one-hundred-dollar bill|$100]] billion it was the leading shampoo in 180 [[countries]].\n\nCurrently, Head & Shoulders is widely available in much of the world. [[Hailee Steinfeld]] and [[Kim Kardashian]] are the current global ambassadors for Head & Shoulders. Head & Shoulders ambassadors for specific countries include [[Joe Taslim]] for Head & Shoulders Indonesia, [[Blackpink]] for Head & Shoulders Korea, China, Hong Kong and Taiwan, [[Iggy Azalea]] for Head & Shoulders Australia, New Zealand and United Kingdom, [[Dua Lipa]] for Head & Shoulders Malaysia and Brunei and [[Lady Gaga]] for Head & Shoulders Singapore and Philippines.\n\n==Ambassadors==\n*[[Hailee Steinfeld]] and [[Kim Kardashian]] (Head & Shoulders United States)\n*[[Joe Taslim]] (Head & Shoulders Indonesia)\n*[[Blackpink]] (Head & Shoulders Korea, China, Hong Kong and Taiwan)\n*[[Iggy Azalea]] (Head & Shoulders Australia, New Zealand and United Kingdom)\n*[[Dua Lipa]] (Head & Shoulders Malaysia and Brunei)\n*[[Lady Gaga]] (Head & Shoulders Singapore and Philippines)\n\n==Slogan==\n'''The World\u2019s No. 1 Shampoo'''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n==External links==\n*{{Official|https://www.headandshoulders.com.au/en-au|Official Website English-Australia}}\n*{{Official|https://www.headandshoulders.co.uk/en-gb|Official Website English-United Kingdom}}\n*{{Official|https://www.headandshoulders.com/|Official Website English-United States}}\n\n{{Procter & Gamble}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Head and Shoulders}}\n[[Category:Shampoo brands]]\n[[Category:Hair care products]]\n[[Category:Skin care]]\n[[Category:Procter & Gamble brands]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 1961]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|a brand of shampoo|the body parts of the same name|Head|and|Shoulder|other uses|Head and shoulders (disambiguation){{!}}Head and shoulders}}\n{{Infobox brand\n| name           = Head & Shoulders\n| logo           = [[File:Head_and_shoulders.png|200px]]\n| type           = Anti-dandruff shampoo\n| currentowner   = [[Procter & Gamble]]\n| previousowners =\n| introduced     = {{start date and age|1961|11}}<ref name=P&Ghist>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZyUwNAs43LcC&lpg=PA427&ots=2hUEAR_pbf&dq=william%20a%20procter%20president&pg=PA423#v=onepage&q=william%20a%20procter%20president&f=false | title=Rising Tide: Lessons from 165 Years of Brand Building at Procter and Gamble | publisher=[[Harvard Business Press]] | date=May 1, 2004 | accessdate=2013-05-07 | author=Davis, Dyer| pages=423|display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n| origin         = [[United States]]\n| markets        = Worldwide\n| website        = {{official URL}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Head and Shoulders in Taguig, Metro Manila.jpg|thumb|250px|The Head & Shoulders sachet in [[Taguig]], [[Metro Manila]], [[Philippines]]]]\n\n'''Head & Shoulders''' ('''H&S''') is an American [[brand]] of anti-[[dandruff]] and non-dandruff [[shampoo]] produced by parent company [[Procter & Gamble]] that was introduced in 1961.<ref name=P&Ghist2>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZyUwNAs43LcC&lpg=PA427&ots=2hUEAR_pbf&dq=william%20a%20procter%20president&pg=PA423#v=onepage&q=william%20a%20procter%20president&f=false | title=Rising Tide: Lessons from 165 Years of Brand Building at Procter and Gamble | publisher=Harvard Business Press | date=May 1, 2004 | accessdate=2013-05-07 | author=Davis, Dyer| pages=423|display-authors=etal}}</ref> \n\nBy 1982, it was the \"number one brand\" of shampoo, and it was noted that \"[n]o one hair care brand gets so many ad dollars as Head & Shoulders, a twenty year old brand, and no other brand matches its sales\", despite it being a \"medicated\" shampoo.<ref>''Marketing & Decisions'' (1982), Volume 17, Issues 8-13, page 186.</ref> Since the 1980s, the brand has long been marketed under the [[tagline]], \"You Never Get a Second Chance to Make a First Impression\", which has been identified as an example of \"anxiety marketing\" commonly used by [[Procter & Gamble]] to drive sales by inducing fears of social consequences associated with the condition that the product claims to address.<ref>Thomas O'Guinn, Chris Allen, Richard J. Semenik, ''Advertising and Integrated Brand Promotion'' (2014), p. 210: \"When Head & Shoulders dandruff shampoo is advertised with the theme \"You Never Get a Second Chance to Make a First Impression\", the audience realizes that Head & Shoulders could spare them the embarrassment of having dandruff\".</ref> In the 2000s, however, sales of the product dropped off, a phenomenon blamed on overextension of the brand into too many varieties, with over thirty kinds of Head & Shoulders being sold.<ref>Matt Haig, ''Brand Failures: The Truth about the 100 Biggest Branding Mistakes of All Time'' (2005), p. 73: \"Procter & Gamble had seen the same thing happen with its Head & Shoulders brand. Did consumers really need 31 varieties of anti-dandruff shampoo?\"</ref> \n\nThe active ingredients in Head & Shoulders are the antifungal agents [[selenium disulfide]] and [[piroctone olamine]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.headandshoulders.co.uk/en-gb/about/ingredients/our-active-ingredients |title=OUR ACTIVE INGREDIENTS |accessdate=16 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n==External links==\n\n*{{Official}}\n\n{{Procter & Gamble}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Head and Shoulders}}\n[[Category:Shampoo brands]]\n[[Category:Hair care products]]\n[[Category:Skin care]]\n[[Category:Procter & Gamble brands]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 1961]]\n", "name_user": "110.137.21.89", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Head_%26_Shoulders"}
